{
  "id": "atoms-auto-mining-perfect",
  "project": "atoms",
  "judge_model": "google/gemini-3-flash-preview",
  "problem": "How can the atoms automatic mining system become much closer to perfect: extract rows as directly and completely as possible, keep validation and labeling separate from extraction, pair success and failure trajectories on the same benchmark instance, enforce post-run validation and fail-closed release gates, and reduce near-duplicate or fake-Gold errors?",
  "target_score": 100,
  "providers": [
    "huggingface_datasets",
    "github_code",
    "github_repos",
    "github_issues"
  ],
  "context_notes": "The local atoms standards say extraction should preserve raw information first, validation should run after extraction rather than inside it, success/failure trajectory pairing matters for SWE-bench-style data, base release must be fail-closed, and semantic dedup plus fake-Gold checks are required. Search should find public implementations or discussions that strengthen those exact dimensions, even when the external projects use different vocabulary.",
